</taxonomicName>
(endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="29E0948B5F69A908FAB0D3232CFFF9A9" box="[1357,1444,1549,1571]" name="Thailand" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">Thailand</collectingCountry>
)
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5148D41B5F69A908FF75D3042CF0F9D1" blockId="3.[136,1452,1376,1916]" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">
<keyLead id="EA06772E5F69A908FF75D3042CF0F9D1" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">
3. Upper glume of the sessile spikelet acute to aristate, not bi-lobed; lower floret epaleate, barren; lower glume of pedicelled spikelet never grooved; callus of pedicelled spikelet never stipe-like, ca. 
<quantity id="960F79FE5F69A908FCC0D3682ADDF9D6" box="[829,902,1606,1628]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="250" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
long.................................................................................4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="EA03CCBE5F69A908FF75D34D2CF1F939" pageId="3" pageNumber="250">
